    intro:
      "The French mountain towns that get discussed most for relocation fall into two categories: the genuinely liveable year-round cities with mountain access (Grenoble, Annecy, Chambéry), and the smaller towns that are lovely in winter but thin on urban infrastructure the rest of the year (most ski resorts). This guide focuses on the former, the places where you can build a life rather than just a ski season.",
