        body: "No large French city has comparable mountain access. Chamrousse ski resort is 40 minutes from the city centre by bus. Les Sept Laux is 50 minutes. Villard-de-Lans (Vercors) is 45 minutes. Autrans is 45 minutes. Alpe d'Huez is 1h15 by car. This means realistic weekday evening skiing in winter (post-work), trail running at altitude on weekday mornings, and access to serious technical mountaineering within an hour of a large city with full urban amenities. The Vercors plateau is accessible by road in 30 minutes and offers hundreds of kilometres of hiking and mountain biking trails. The Chartreuse massif to the north is quieter, a more spiritual landscape, and equally accessible.",
