        body: "Based on relocation patterns: **#1 Annecy** (the dominant quality-of-life upgrade destination). **#2 Bordeaux** (career and lifestyle upgrade, similar quality, milder climate). **#3 Aix-en-Provence** (Mediterranean, family-friendly). **#4 Nantes** (Atlantic, family-friendly, similar professional ecosystem). **#5 Dijon** (smaller scale, TGV-connected, wine country). **#6 Montpellier** (warmer, more affordable, dynamic). **#7 Saint-Étienne** (affordable Lyon-orbit alternative). **#8 Chambéry** (mountain lifestyle with a smaller-city pace). Beyond these top 8: the Geneva area (frontalier), Grenoble (urban plus mountain), Strasbourg (Franco-German), Toulouse (aerospace), Marseille (Mediterranean urban scale). For internationally-oriented Lyon-leavers, Geneva and Brussels are also common, given the jobs in international institutions and the EU branches of multinationals.",
