        body: "Rennes (220,000 city, 420,000 metropolitan) is the Brittany capital. It is historically Breton, with the language still visible in bilingual street signs and a strong cultural identity, a medieval core partially surrounded by 18th-century Parisian-style urban fabric, and an unusually dense cluster of grandes écoles (Sciences Po Rennes, INSA Rennes, ENS Rennes). Its 73,000 students give it a young, intellectual energy. Nantes (320,000 city, 650,000 metropolitan) is the Loire-Atlantique capital, France's 6th city by metropolitan area, and somewhat larger in feel, with more variety of neighbourhoods, a stronger art and creative scene (Machines de l'île, the Lieu Unique), and a larger tech cluster. Nantes consistently ranks first in surveys of the most livable French city.",
