        body: "Both cities have invested heavily in tech cluster development. Rennes is the French cybersecurity capital (Inria, Orange Cyberdefense, Thales), with a strong telecom sector (Bouygues and SFR both have major engineering bases here) and growing deeptech. Nantes is stronger in digital and creative industries, hosts Airbus headquarters for the Atlantic programmes (Saint-Nazaire is 55km away), and has a larger general business ecosystem. For a software engineer or cybersecurity specialist, Rennes is arguably the more interesting job market. For a generalist, or someone in logistics, manufacturing, or creative industries, Nantes offers more breadth.",
