        body: "Rennes brings you into the Brittany world: crêpes and galettes, cider culture, the Breton language and cultural identity, and access to the extraordinary Brittany coastline (Saint-Malo 55min, Dinard, Mont Saint-Michel 1h). The landscape is greener, the sea is wilder, and the cultural identity is more distinctly non-Parisian than almost anywhere in France. Nantes has its own identity, historically the capital of the Breton duchy and now firmly in Loire-Atlantique, with access to the Atlantic beaches (the Jade Coast, Noirmoutier, île d'Yeu) and to Loire wine appellations (Muscadet, Coteaux de la Loire). The choice between them is partly a question of which Atlantic identity resonates more.",
