        heading: "The verdict",
        body: "Bordeaux wins for those who want slightly better climate (especially autumn through spring), wine and Gascony food culture as a central life interest, a slightly more sophisticated urban aesthetic (the 18th-century UNESCO centre is uniformly elegant in a way Nantes is not), and proximity to the Dordogne and Périgord for weekend escapes. Nantes wins for those who rank quality-of-life metrics above aesthetic beauty, people who want a city with more varied urban character and a stronger arts scene, those who prioritise Paris access (Nantes is TGV 2h05, Bordeaux 2h10, but Nantes is less exposed to the high-season price pressures the Bordeaux TGV created), and families who want the best overall combination of schools, healthcare, and infrastructure.",
