        heading: "Property prices and where to live",
        body: "Bordeaux's property market stratified sharply after 2017, thanks to the TGV effect. Current averages run as follows. Chartrons and the Triangle d'Or (the historic bourgeois districts, the most desirable) run €4,500–6,500/m². Saint-Michel and Victoire (the student and bohemian quarter, south of the centre) run €3,200–4,500/m². La Bastide (right bank, across the Garonne, up-and-coming) runs €2,800–3,800/m². Mériadeck and Bordeaux Lac (northwest) run €3,000–4,000/m². Caudéran (an inner suburb of houses with gardens) runs €3,200–4,200/m². Monthly rent for a 75m² flat runs €1,100–1,700 in the central quartiers. La Bastide offers the best value for those willing to be across the river.",
