        body: "On healthcare, the CHU de Bordeaux is comprehensive. GP access requires patience, with a 2 to 3 month wait for new patients in popular areas. English-speaking doctors are available but require active searching, so check the Doctolib filters. On transport, the Bordeaux tram (4 lines, covering most key destinations) is excellent, and Vélo'V bike-sharing is widely used. A car is optional in the centre but useful for Médoc and vineyard weekends. TGV to Paris takes 2h04, one of the best provincial connections, and driving to Spain (San Sebastián) takes 2h15. On schools, the International School of Bordeaux (Talence) offers an English curriculum to Baccalaureate, and several public lycées have sections internationales with bilingual English-French streams.",
