    intro: "Nantes is the value play of France's Atlantic west: a city of about 320,000 with the working economy of a much bigger one (digital, biotech, agri-food, the old naval yards), an hour from the coast and two hours from Paris by TGV. Prices climbed roughly 45% over a decade through 2022, then gave back about 6% in 2024-2025. That correction is your window. This guide maps Nantes neighbourhood by neighbourhood, in euros per square metre, and explains how the French buying process actually works if you are coming from abroad. No residency is required to buy, the figures here are real, and nothing is dressed up.",
